metadata.name: Heat Death #629
metadata.description:
Heat Death is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

It aims to produce variation and detail from minimal logic.

The source code uses p5.js and consists of around 180 lines of code. It has been left unminified for the interested viewer to learn more.

metadata.name: Kunza #9
metadata.description:
In 1949, the last known native speaker of Kunza died in the Atacama desert of Chile, leaving behind only fragments of a language that stretched back to when the Incans ruled the region. The textures, patterns, and colors in this project are not intended to be historically accurate: they tell a story. They are my attempt to reach into the past and imagine a vibrant history that is increasingly inaccessible.

Features include weave design, symbol layout, symbol style, and color palette.

After the image has fully rendered, pressing ‚Äòw‚Äô, ‚Äòr‚Äô, or ‚Äòc‚Äô will toggle different elements of the image, and pressing ‚Äòs‚Äô will download a PNG file.

p5.js

metadata.name: Gestalt #540
metadata.description:
"Gestalt" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

A flurry of many elements derived from my past (and future) strewn across a single canvas. As random as things seem, collectively time tends to reveal hints of order in the chaos. Sometimes, more is more.

Controls:
‚Ä¢ Left-click/tap reassembles the piece with one less element each time

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #200
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: Dancer Lines #73
metadata.description:
Before I write anything about this project, I request you to see the project variations carefully because I spent a lot of time getting it up and running quickly. You can see some of them on my Twitter.

Changing the size and angle of the lines randomly and repeating them in a regular series will produce extraordinary shapes in Euclidean geometry. Regular and identical proportions can be used in architecture and artistic patterns, while irregular and fractal proportions are used in the creation of intricate works of art.

this artwork can be seen in 1, 2, or 3 layers layered on top of each other, with different shadows and transparency. In order to maintain the unique beauty of each work, I have avoided placing a rarity value on it.
 
You can save the artwork you want by pressing the "s" key.

made with p5js
@NatinaCode

metadata.name: Creta Sarculum #34
metadata.description:
An exploration of simple chalk rake designs. 

Each piece has a few key variables, probabilities for those variables are as follows:

75% Gradient Background
25% Solid Color Background
4.76% Each Chalk Color Palette (21 palettes)
50% Circular Modifier
25% Rectangular Modifier
15% Rectangular Gradient Modifier

Press 's' in Live View to save a full resolution image.
